\": 328}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, those who make it to the podium this year will receive their medal and a surprise gift box, reportedly containing an Olympics poster and a plushie of the mascot, the red triangular Phryge.\", \"from\": 330, \"to\": 527, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 360, \"to\": 370}, {\"ngram\": \"their medal\", \"from\": 394, \"to\": 405}, {\"ngram\": \"a surprise gift box\", \"from\": 410, \"to\": 429}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympics poster\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 471}, {\"ngram\": \"a plushie\", \"from\": 476, \"to\": 485}, {\"ngram\": \"the mascot\", \"from\": 489, \"to\": 499}, {\"ngram\": \"the red triangular Phryge\", \"from\": 501, \"to\": 526}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The responsibility for prize pots and financial assistance before the games falls to the National Olympic Committees.\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 646, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 618, \"end\": 645, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999329321953718, \"rank\": 6.70723031006562e-05, \"text\": \"National Olympic Committees\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The responsibility\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 547}, {\"ngram\": \"prize pots\", \"from\": 552, \"to\": 562}, {\"ngram\": \"financial assistance\", \"from\": 567, \"to\": 587}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 595, \"to\": 604}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, World Athletics and the International Boxing Association have announced they will be distributing some prize money this year.\", \"from\": 647, \"to\": 783, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 658, \"end\": 673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999990518518, \"rank\": 9.48049087395856e-10, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 682, \"end\": 714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2786982343860903e-15, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some prize money\", \"from\": 756, \"to\": 772}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The UK is among the few countries that do not provide a direct cash reward for podium placements.\", \"from\": 785, \"to\": 882, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 789, \"end\": 791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999974070306, \"rank\": 2.5928168991667305e-09, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the few countries\", \"from\": 801, \"to\": 818}, {\"ngram\": \"a direct cash reward\", \"from\": 839, \"to\": 859}, {\"ngram\": \"podium placements\", \"from\": 864, \"to\": 881}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, British Athletics has taken the initiative to offer medal bonuses separate from the government.\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 987, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 892, \"end\": 899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999999930137164, \"rank\": 3.7559737724117884e-09, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the initiative\", \"from\": 920, \"to\": 934}, {\"ngram\": \"medal bonuses\", \"from\": 944, \"to\": 957}, {\"ngram\": \"the government\", \"from\": 972, \"to\": 986}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB instead receives grants before their Olympic appearance to fund their training and increase their chances of podium finishes.\", \"from\": 989, \"to\": 1122, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Team GB\", \"from\": 989, \"to\": 996}, {\"ngram\": \"grants\", \"from\": 1014, \"to\": 1020}, {\"ngram\": \"their Olympic appearance\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1052}, {\"ngram\": \"their training\", \"from\": 1061, \"to\": 1075}, {\"ngram\": \"their chances\", \"from\": 1089, \"to\": 1102}, {\"ngram\": \"podium finishes\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1121}]}, {\"sentence\": \"READ MORE:Transgender boxer wants Imane Khelif banned from Olympics as gender row explodes Asreported by CNBC, Hong Kong tops the list in rewarding its elite athletes, dishing out a whopping $768,000 (\\u00a3603,000) for Olympic gold medallists, while silver and bronze bring home $384,000 (\\u00a3301,000) and $192,000 (\\u00a3150,000) respectively.\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1134, \"end\": 1145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\", \"score\": 0.999999999992724, \"rank\": 7.0555951067851254e-12, \"text\": \"Transgender\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\"}, {\"begin\": 1158, \"end\": 1170, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}, {\"begin\": 1230, \"end\": 1234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"score\": 0.9999999501042124, \"rank\": 4.989577246236544e-08, \"text\": \"CNBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNBC\"}, {\"begin\": 1236, \"end\": 1245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\", \"score\": 0.9999998636763032, \"rank\": 1.2734573048693294e-07, \"text\": \"Hong Kong\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hong_Kong\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympics\", \"from\": 1183, \"to\": 1191}, {\"ngram\": \"the list\", \"from\": 1250, \"to\": 1258}, {\"ngram\": \"its elite athletes\", \"from\": 1272, \"to\": 1290}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic gold medallists\", \"from\": 1339, \"to\": 1362}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 1370, \"to\": 1376}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 1381, \"to\": 1387}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Singapore offers similar lucrative rewards, and Indonesia is not far behind, providing $300,000 (\\u00a3235,000) for gold, with silver and bronze winners receiving lesser amounts.\", \"from\": 1458, \"to\": 1631, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1458, \"end\": 1467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.586243598655778e-12, \"text\": \"Singapore\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore\"}, {\"begin\": 1506, \"end\": 1515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"score\": 0.9999999673159442, \"rank\": 3.126134845607594e-08, \"text\": \"Indonesia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indonesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"similar lucrative rewards\", \"from\": 1475, \"to\": 1500}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1569, \"to\": 1573}, {\"ngram\": \"silver and bronze winners\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1605}, {\"ngram\": \"lesser amounts\", \"from\": 1616, \"to\": 1630}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In contrast, Germany's Sports Aid Foundation extends financial rewards beyond the top three, reaching out to those securing up to the 8th position.\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1780, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1646, \"end\": 1653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.9679385984686919, \"rank\": 0.031888604001179294, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"contrast\", \"from\": 1636, \"to\": 1644}, {\"ngram\": \"financial rewards\", \"from\": 1686, \"to\": 1703}, {\"ngram\": \"the 8th position\", \"from\": 1763, \"to\": 1779}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the other end of the pay scale, Australia's rewards are modest at best, offering $13,000 (\\u00a310,000) for gold, with smaller sums for other medals.\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 1928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1816, \"end\": 1825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999978414880947, \"rank\": 1.933280153553359e-06, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the other end\", \"from\": 1784, \"to\": 1797}, {\"ngram\": \"the pay scale\", \"from\": 1801, \"to\": 1814}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1887, \"to\": 1891}, {\"ngram\": \"smaller sums\", \"from\": 1898, \"to\": 1910}, {\"ngram\": \"other medals\", \"from\": 1915, \"to\": 1927}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, it's not just about the money.\", \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 1969, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the money\", \"from\": 1959, \"to\": 1968}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes often benefit from additional perks for instance, gold medal winners from Kazakhstan receive $250,000 (\\u00a3196,000) as well as housing.\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 2111, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2053, \"end\": 2063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan\", \"score\": 0.9999999949081939, \"rank\": 4.0517924785671685e-09, \"text\": \"Kazakhstan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Athletes\", \"from\": 1970, \"to\": 1978}, {\"ngram\": \"additional perks\", \"from\": 1998, \"to\": 2014}, {\"ngram\": \"instance\", \"from\": 2019, \"to\": 2027}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medal winners\", \"from\": 2029, \"to\": 2047}, {\"ngram\": \"housing\", \"from\": 2103, \"to\": 2110}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Malaysian athletes too can strike gold beyond government provisions, with the Malaysian National Sports Council offering $215,000(\\u00a3168,000)-$22,000 (\\u00a317,000).\", \"from\": 2113, \"to\": 2271, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2113, \"end\": 2131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Malaysian athletes\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2191, \"end\": 2200, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia\", \"score\": 0.9959683057075834, \"rank\": 0.004041432917218565, \"text\": \"Malaysian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Malaysia\"}, {\"begin\": 2201, \"end\": 2224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sport_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999630255152593, \"rank\": 3.6975830528157794e-05, \"text\": \"National Sports Council\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sport_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sport_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 2147, \"to\": 2151}, {\"ngram\": \"government provisions\", \"from\": 2159, \"to\": 2180}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Local companies add to the pot with lavish apartments and cash bonuses, plus a \\\"foreign-made car\\\" has been promised by Youth and Sports Minister Hannah Yeoh according 